<item>
            <title>[SOLR-11424] When legacyCloud=false, cores should not publish itself as DOWN on startup</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-11424</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When we load CoreContainer, we already publish a DOWNNODE operation to ZK. Which publish all its cores as DOWN. &lt;br/&gt;
Then each of its cores publishes itself as DOWN. These are wasted operations in case of legacyCloud=false.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
